title: Moderate realism
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A belief within [[Realism]]; particulars are all that truly exists in the material world, and universals are the indistinct qualities that classify them.

A belief within realism that states that [[Particulars]] are all that exist, while [[Universals]] are only qualities that are not distinct from the particular. It has a lot of similarities to [[Nominalism]], only it argues for the existence of universals despite their indistinctiveness from particulars.
